<dl id="n53093o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53093o">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53093o"> 93(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> table round <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53093o"><li>FW 285.03 </li><li><a href="../../flex/lg/lexlg.htm#n53093o">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/lg/l39lg.htm#n53093o">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53093o">MS BL 47478-68v</ms> </li><li>JJA 53:202 <a name="lgd12" href="../../FF/fdra/lda.htm#lgd12">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/lg/lgd12.htm#n53093o">Draft: II.2&sect;8.12</a></li> </ul> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53093o"></li><li>FW 266.11 </li><li><a href="../../flex/lb/lexlb.htm#n53093o">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/lb/l39lb.htm#n53093o">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53093o">MS BL 47478-332</ms> </li><li>JJA 53:311 <a name="lad13" href="../../FF/fdra/lda.htm#lbd11">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/lb/lbd11.htm#n53093o">Draft: II.2&sect;2.11</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Wace&apos;s literary celebrity is due, perhaps, most of all to the fact that he is the first Arthurian writer to mention the Round Table. &ldquo;The Bretons,&rdquo; he says, &ldquo;tell many a fable of the <mark>Table Round</mark>,&rdquo; but he does not explain whence such fables came, or where he heard them told. He does, however, inform us that the Table was made round because each of Arthur&apos;s knights thought himself better than his fellows, and Arthur devised this method of settling all disputes about precedence among them. The praise of the knights of the Round Table, he adds in another place, was loud throughout the world. <small> W. Lewis Jones, <a name="WJKA3" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WJKA3"><cite title="source">King Arthur in History and Legend</cite></a> (1914) 90f</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n25106e" href="n25all.htm#n25106e">N25 (VI.B.15):106(e)</a> and <a name="n25106f" href="n25all.htm#n25106f">N25 (VI.B.15):106(f)</a>. On p.93 we learn that &lsquo;the Round Table was constructed by a strange carpenter from oversea.&rsquo;. </mm> </dd></dl>
